The National Capital Region has started administering the 2nd dose for the HCW vaccinees, maximizing protection for our healthcare workers.

With the recent arrival of 1M doses of procured vaccines, the total number of available doses have doubled, and doses distributed throughout the country have significantly increased, with a total of 1,468,200 doses delivered.

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX

What to do after vaccination What should you do if you experience local reactions after vaccination? How to stop the spread of COVID-19 even after vaccination?
Know the right answers to these frequently asked questions on how you can protect yourself and your family from COVID-19

Q: Can you get infected even after vaccination? 
A: Yes, there's still a possibility that you can get COVID-19 after you get vaccinated. COVID-19 vaccines can protect you from getting symptomatic COVID-19 and it can prevent hospitalization and death from the disease.

Q: Can you get infected with COVID-19 from the vaccine? 
A: NO. You cannot get COVID-19 from the vaccine as there is no live virus in any of the vaccines presently available. https://t.co/OBfoZ8IxHX
